not end up in a six-by-nine

32:16.935 --> 32:19.405
with Eva fighting over
our top bunk.

32:19.438 --> 32:20.906
Never gonna happen.

32:20.939 --> 32:22.308
-MICHAEL: Hey.
-Hey.

32:22.341 --> 32:24.276
I need to borrow
Harry's computer.

32:24.310 --> 32:26.812
They confiscated mine.
You have any idea where it is?

32:26.845 --> 32:30.616
Probably in the same evidence
lockup downtown as yours.

32:30.649 --> 32:33.585
Wait, what?
They took his, too?

32:33.619 --> 32:35.921
The hell... What are they
thinking? He-He's robbing banks

32:35.954 --> 32:37.990
-and playing Minecraft?
-Listen, I don't know.

32:38.024 --> 32:39.858
Like father, like son, I guess.

32:39.891 --> 32:41.860
Tell me you didn't spend
the better part of your day

32:41.893 --> 32:44.596
helping my fiancé
bust open a vault?

32:44.630 --> 32:46.432
We were trying to save Hen.

32:46.465 --> 32:48.334
-Thank you for that, by the way.
-You got it.

32:48.367 --> 32:49.835
I think.

32:49.868 --> 32:51.003
(phone vibrating)

32:51.037 --> 32:52.704
(sighs)

32:52.738 --> 32:55.174
It's the hospital.

32:55.207 --> 32:58.044
Hello?
Yes, this is she.

33:00.512 --> 33:03.315
Place looks pretty good.
Wh-What happened--

33:03.349 --> 33:05.617
-you-you clean up
after they left?
-Mm-mmm.

33:05.651 --> 33:07.719
Police were very careful.

33:07.753 --> 33:09.355
-(phone chimes)
-(Michael chuckles)

33:09.388 --> 33:10.622
-You mean terrified...
-Ah.

33:10.656 --> 33:12.491
of you.

33:12.524 --> 33:15.061
-(chuckles)
-They got my tox report back.

33:15.094 --> 33:17.463
You'll never believe
what they found.

33:17.496 --> 33:18.730
Scorpion venom.

33:21.400 --> 33:24.236
I feel robbed. How in the hell
did you know that?

33:24.270 --> 33:27.673
It was in the hand sanitizer
that you found in the vault.

33:27.706 --> 33:29.641
Uh, what is that
supposed to mean?

33:29.675 --> 33:32.911
I have no idea.
(laughs)

33:32.944 --> 33:35.514
But... you do.

33:35.547 --> 33:36.782
HEN:
Yeah.

33:39.017 --> 33:40.086
I know who did this.

33:59.071 --> 34:01.273
Hey, Marty, thanks for coming.

34:01.307 --> 34:04.243
Hey. Yeah, I heard you guys were
having trouble with the ladder.

34:04.276 --> 34:07.079
Was starting to think you guys,
uh, don't know how to use it.

34:07.113 --> 34:08.280
(truck door opens)

34:08.314 --> 34:09.915
Well, you know how we operate.

34:09.948 --> 34:12.184
All our procedures
and protocols.

34:12.218 --> 34:14.220
BUCK:
But maybe you could
show us some tricks.

34:14.253 --> 34:17.356
Yeah, you seem to know more
about these trucks than we do.

34:17.389 --> 34:19.858
Like, where to hide
$300,000 in cash.

34:19.891 --> 34:23.629
(laughs)
What are you guys talking about?

34:23.662 --> 34:25.264
How are your hands, Marty?

34:25.297 --> 34:28.600
That alternative medicine
still working?

34:39.511 --> 34:41.647
WASH:
Marty Collins.

34:41.680 --> 34:45.451
You're under arrest
for bank robbery and murder.

34:45.484 --> 34:49.255
Murder?
Who'd I kill?

34:51.523 --> 34:54.560
WASH:
The armored car courier--

34:54.593 --> 34:57.996
he died from an allergic
reaction to scorpion venom.

34:58.029 --> 35:00.098
That's what's in the bottle,

35:00.132 --> 35:02.434
in concentrated gel form.

35:02.468 --> 35:05.003
MERCER:
That's what you've been using
to combat your arthritis.

35:05.036 --> 35:08.140
Sorry, I totally
had to google this.

35:08.174 --> 35:11.777
"The iberiotoxin blocks
the potassium channels

35:11.810 --> 35:14.012
that allow arthritis
to spread through the bones."

35:14.045 --> 35:17.616
An overdose of the stuff mimics
the symptoms of a nerve agent.

35:17.649 --> 35:19.017
WASH:
Creating just enough chaos
so you can impersonate

35:19.050 --> 35:20.919
a real firefighter...

35:20.952 --> 35:24.290
and get that armored car driver
away from his truck, right?

35:25.824 --> 35:27.326
ATHENA:
Is that the guy?

35:27.359 --> 35:29.328
SAM:
I'm not sure.

35:29.361 --> 35:30.962
(sighs)

35:30.996 --> 35:33.365
* Wimoweh... *

35:33.399 --> 35:35.534
Yeah.

35:35.567 --> 35:37.536
That's him.

35:37.569 --> 35:40.506
BUCK:
So let's see
if I got this right.

35:40.539 --> 35:43.942
The fake nerve agent attack
was a distraction

35:43.975 --> 35:46.845
for the armored car robbery...

35:46.878 --> 35:48.280
which was a distraction

35:48.314 --> 35:50.849
for the diamond heist.

35:50.882 --> 35:53.519
-Crime is hard.
-(chuckles)

35:53.552 --> 35:56.888
Franklin knew the bank
and Marty knew us.

35:56.922 --> 35:58.156
But how'd they know each other?

35:58.190 --> 36:00.726
Brothers-in-law.
Well, ex-brothers-in-law.

36:00.759 --> 36:04.296
Franklin had been married
to Marty's crazy sister.

36:04.330 --> 36:07.899
And when they ran into each
other again, a plan formed.

36:07.933 --> 36:09.335
Franklin was the inside man.

36:09.368 --> 36:12.003
His job was to create a
medical emergency in the bank.

36:12.037 --> 36:15.674
The kind that would trigger
a hazmat response because Marty

36:15.707 --> 36:17.243
knew that we'd have
to seal the perimeter

36:17.276 --> 36:19.478
to execute
the Big Bird protocol.

36:19.511 --> 36:22.414
-The money's fine.
-MARTY: You're in danger!

36:22.448 --> 36:24.316
HEN:
He gets the driver
to leave the truck

36:24.350 --> 36:26.585
and empty all his pockets.

36:26.618 --> 36:28.420
And while the driver
gets clean, Marty gets rich.

36:31.223 --> 36:33.559
Except, how's he gonna get
all that money out of there?

36:36.895 --> 36:38.697
Can't just walk it
off the scene.

36:38.730 --> 36:41.433
He needed a mule.

36:42.868 --> 36:45.737
Or a team of mules. Us.

37:00.419 --> 37:03.455
Not a bad plan. I mean, it's
crazy, but it could've worked.

37:03.489 --> 37:05.123
We bring the money back here
and all he has to do

37:05.156 --> 37:06.358
is wait for the right moment,

37:06.392 --> 37:08.560
sneak in,
access the ladder truck

37:08.594 --> 37:10.362
and retrieve the money.
Except there wasn't any,

37:10.396 --> 37:12.531
because the police had already
beaten him to the punch.

37:12.564 --> 37:14.466
(song in foreign language
playing)

37:18.670 --> 37:21.807
But how'd the police know
exactly where to find the money?

37:21.840 --> 37:24.242
'Cause there was one variable
that Marty didn't count on.

37:25.344 --> 37:26.612
The double-cross.

37:30.282 --> 37:32.284
See, Marty may have known
everything there is to know

37:32.318 --> 37:35.721
about LAFD protocol, but
Franklin knew about the bank.

37:35.754 --> 37:37.556
He knew what was in that vault.

37:37.589 --> 37:39.491
He could steal those diamonds
with his eyes closed.

37:41.159 --> 37:44.463
See, Marty's plan was simple,

37:44.496 --> 37:45.931
but Franklin's was
more time-sensitive,

37:45.964 --> 37:48.233
so he told Marty
the best day to rob

37:48.266 --> 37:50.268
the armored car
would be his last day.

37:50.302 --> 37:52.638
He knew there'd be a party
at the end of day,

37:52.671 --> 37:54.272
at the close of business.

37:54.306 --> 37:56.308
He'd start with Marty's plan,

37:56.342 --> 37:57.509
then he'd improvise.

38:00.679 --> 38:02.514
Franklin made sure
he collapsed inside the vault.

38:02.548 --> 38:04.383
He knew what
our response would be.

38:06.151 --> 38:07.419
911, what's your emergency?

38:07.453 --> 38:08.854
CHIMNEY:
Then all he had to do was wait

38:08.887 --> 38:09.855
for the vault
to automatically close

38:09.888 --> 38:12.090
and time-seal for the night.

38:12.123 --> 38:13.492
Then he'd have hours alone
inside that vault

38:13.525 --> 38:16.194
while we ran
our rescue protocols.

38:17.396 --> 38:18.830
It was meticulous plan.

38:18.864 --> 38:21.199
But there was
an unexpected complication.

38:22.334 --> 38:23.702
Me.

38:23.735 --> 38:25.971
He was supposed
to be in there alone.

38:26.004 --> 38:29.375
So me running in to save
his sorry ass? A complication.

38:29.408 --> 38:30.976
He had to take me out, too.

38:31.009 --> 38:33.211
* I've been caught stealing... *

38:33.244 --> 38:35.280
But now he's playing
"beat the clock."

38:35.313 --> 38:38.283
Soon as the cameras
couldn't see,

38:38.316 --> 38:41.553
Franklin swiped
six million in stones

38:41.587 --> 38:42.821
and waited to be saved.

38:42.854 --> 38:44.289
He had the stones.

38:44.322 --> 38:46.692
All he needed
was a clean getaway.

38:46.725 --> 38:48.727
MAN:
L.A. Department
of Robbery and Homicide.

38:48.760 --> 38:51.630
Yes, I have information
on an armored car robbery.

38:51.663 --> 38:55.867
HEN:
He sends the police after us.

38:55.901 --> 38:58.404
So, while the police
are investigating us...

38:58.437 --> 39:00.205
he could flee the country.

39:00.238 --> 39:03.241
-New name,
new passport, new life.
-He just wasn't fast enough.

39:03.274 --> 39:05.343
Marty knew he'd been
double-crossed.

39:05.377 --> 39:06.578
He goes to confront Franklin.

39:06.612 --> 39:08.714
Marty, l-look,
I can explain it to you.

39:08.747 --> 39:11.149
Where you going, Franklin?

39:11.182 --> 39:13.218
-Where's the money?
Did you double-cross me?
-Everything's gonna work...

39:13.251 --> 39:15.220
-no, I swear to you. I...
-Did you double-cross me?!

39:15.253 --> 39:18.490
No, I...
(choking, grunting)

39:18.524 --> 39:20.225
So Marty killed Franklin.

39:22.528 --> 39:24.329
What?

39:24.362 --> 39:26.565
-I didn't kill nobody.
-What about the dead guard?

39:26.598 --> 39:29.067
It was supposed
to be non-lethal.

39:29.100 --> 39:30.702
I mean, that's why we used it.

39:30.736 --> 39:33.505
How was I supposed to know
he was allergic?

39:33.539 --> 39:35.607
But I never touched Franklin.

39:35.641 --> 39:38.610
You have been charged with
two counts of felony murder,

39:38.644 --> 39:41.379
grand theft,
reckless endangerment and

39:41.413 --> 39:45.050
-impersonating a firefighter.
-You can make this easier
on yourself.

39:45.083 --> 39:46.785
Just tell us.

39:46.818 --> 39:48.887
Where are the diamonds?

39:50.221 --> 39:52.924
Diamonds?

39:52.958 --> 39:54.192
What diamonds?

39:54.225 --> 39:55.827
There are diamonds?

39:57.929 --> 39:59.230
You believe him?

39:59.264 --> 40:01.232
I don't know.

40:01.266 --> 40:03.635
MERCER:
He admitted to everything
but killing Franklin

40:03.669 --> 40:07.072
-and stealing the diamonds.
-So where are they?

40:07.105 --> 40:09.007
*

40:23.188 --> 40:26.825
Stomach contents include corn,

40:26.858 --> 40:31.329
some sort of grain--
possibly quinoa--

40:31.362 --> 40:34.700
and some sort of foreign mass.

40:37.936 --> 40:41.640
Appears to be... a diamond.

41:02.060 --> 41:03.995
(stomach rumbles)

41:06.131 --> 41:08.366
(grunts)

41:08.399 --> 41:10.435
(laughter)

41:10.468 --> 41:12.838
BOBBY:
Mm.

41:12.871 --> 41:15.306
-What are they putting
on the death certificate?
-Oh, my...

41:15.340 --> 41:17.442
"Acute intestinal blockage."

41:17.475 --> 41:19.678
They rejected my suggestion.

41:19.711 --> 41:22.113
-"Cause of death: greed."
-(laughs)

41:22.147 --> 41:23.982
(knocking on door)

41:36.194 --> 41:38.697
Chief.
This is a surprise.

41:38.730 --> 41:41.066
-Sorry to bother you at home.
-Uh, it's okay.

41:41.099 --> 41:43.501
Come on in.

41:43.535 --> 41:45.571
Chief Alonzo, this is
Athena Grant, my fiancée.

41:47.606 --> 41:49.307
Pleasure to meet you, ma'am.

41:49.340 --> 41:51.009
Uh, I should go.

41:51.042 --> 41:52.410
I'd rather you stayed.

41:52.443 --> 41:54.746
If that's okay with you, Chief.

41:57.282 --> 41:59.885
There's no way to ease
into this conversation.

41:59.918 --> 42:02.954
Believe me, I tried to find one
on the drive here.

42:04.790 --> 42:07.726
LAPD has referred a matter
to us for further review,

42:07.759 --> 42:10.562
based on some irregularities

42:10.596 --> 42:12.764
they found during
their investigation.

42:12.798 --> 42:15.901
The bank robbery investigation?
I thought the team was cleared.

42:15.934 --> 42:17.803
Team was.
You weren't.

42:19.137 --> 42:21.539
I think you know why.

42:21.573 --> 42:23.441
You'll be on suspended duty

42:23.474 --> 42:25.711
pending a full inquiry.

42:25.744 --> 42:28.346
We have a lot of questions.

42:28.379 --> 42:31.349
Until they're answered
to our satisfaction,

42:31.382 --> 42:33.719
you are relieved
of your command, Captain Nash.

42:34.953 --> 42:36.755
ATHENA:
Just one minute, now.

42:36.788 --> 42:38.223
You need to explain yourself.

42:38.256 --> 42:41.526
For what reason
are you relieving him of duty?

42:41.559 --> 42:43.695
Captain Nash lied to us

42:43.729 --> 42:46.431
-when he joined the LAFD.
-About what?

42:46.464 --> 42:48.399
About what happened
in Minnesota.

43:05.817 --> 43:08.754
Captioned by
Media Access Group at WGBH

43:35.280 --> 43:37.582
You've answered the call
on 9-1-1.

43:37.615 --> 43:39.851
Now here are a few more shows
to check out from Fox.

43:42.320 --> 43:44.990
Rule number one
if you want to stay alive.

43:45.023 --> 43:46.925
Don't lie to your doctor.

43:46.958 --> 43:50.095
* Show me how to come alive *

43:50.128 --> 43:53.164
-Profits over patients, again.
-You save your morality lesson.

43:53.198 --> 43:54.532
-WOMAN:
You have to save him!
-(long tone)

43:54.565 --> 43:56.634
-(coughs)
-Be careful.

43:56.668 --> 43:58.670
-You tried to kill him.
-I had no choice!

43:58.704 --> 44:02.007
-(siren wailing)
-* Let me know I'm not alone *

44:02.674 --> 44:04.042
Shall we?

44:04.075 --> 44:06.878
* Show me how to come alive *

44:06.912 --> 44:10.181
ANNOUNCER: The Resident,
all new, Mondays at 8:00 on Fox.

44:12.851 --> 44:14.886
COOKIE:
We did bad things,
Lucious.

44:14.920 --> 44:17.355
And it's coming back
to collect

44:17.388 --> 44:20.225
with a living, breathing,
furious man

44:20.258 --> 44:22.027
who calls you
"Daddy."

44:22.060 --> 44:24.562
I am your flesh and blood,
and you don't give a damn.

44:24.595 --> 44:27.032
ANNOUNCER:
Miss a moment
of Empire?

44:27.065 --> 44:28.666
He could destroy
everything we've built.

44:30.401 --> 44:32.403
I took the thing
that you value most,

44:32.437 --> 44:34.672
and I toyed with it
for my own entertainment.

44:35.774 --> 44:36.975
We gotta take him down.

44:37.008 --> 44:39.044
ANNOUNCER:
Empire, Wednesday.
